    <h3>B. Answer the following questions.</h3>
    <p>
        <strong>a. How do you define social media? </strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>	Social media can be defined as a collective term of web sites and applications that enable users to create and share content or to participate in building the virtual networks and communities.<br><br>
        <strong>b. Social media has been an integral part of modern life. How?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>	Social media help us to communicate with people around the world; give us the chance to send and receive information, and get many updates from people following and being a part of a new marketing strategy. In this modern world people are physically far apart from one another nationally or internationally. These virtual media like Facebook, twitter, Instagram, skype and other applications can virtually keep them near to each other despite their physical distance. So, it has been an integral part of modern life.<br><br>
        <strong>c. Why do people use Facebook and You Tube ?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>	People use Facebook to stay in touch with your loved ones, get up to date information and news. Similarly people use YouTube to watch important video and share their video. <br><br>
        <strong>d. What is a blog? How can it be beneficial to us? </strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>	A blog is an informational website where a person writes regularly about recent topics that interest him/her. It can be beneficial to us as it allows us to share "What we think" about articles, pictures, current issues, videos and so on. Blogs can also be used for advertisement purpose.<br><br>
        <strong>e. Was Prita's intention bad when she sent a message to her friends? </strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>	No, it wasn't. She just tried to remind her friends to be more selective in choosing the hospital and to be more careful in accepting many kinds of services. <br><br>
        <strong>f. How did Prita's message become a big problem?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>	Prita's message became a big problem after her friends shared it to a website (The people's forum) which so many read and commented on the issue.<br><br>
        <strong>g.Why was she convicted by the court? </strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>	She was convicted by the court for violating the law about using ICT.<br><br>
        <strong>h. What was the purpose of the campaign, "Bantu Bedaskan Prita"? </strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>	The purpose of the campaign 'Bantu Bedaskan Prita' was to collect money to help Prita so that she could pay the amercement.<br><br>
        <strong>i. How are people stronger than social media?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>	People are stronger than social media as they can easily think before they act and think before they speak.<br><br>
    </p>
    <h2>Critical Thinking</h2>
    <p>
        <strong>a. Does social media have positive impact in the society? Discuss. </strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>	Social media have positive impacts in the society. The platforms like Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, Viber, etc have assisted us to connect ourselves to family members, friends and relatives who may be living in different corners of the world. Those social networking sites support people to share pictures and videos, and communicate with the people of their choice. This makes our relationships stronger and brings families together in a way that was impossible in the past.
        <br><br> Professional websites and official organizational web pages create numerous chances to explore the world, learn new facts and read the new survey results, reports, etc. There is remarkable increase in online learning and build a strong profession around it. It is interesting to mention that the person who involves in business can be benefited from social media, too, Online promotions are less expensive than consistent ads on TV channels and newspapers. On the other hand, they give chance to reach the wider audience and find active customers across the world. Through interaction with customers and feedbacks given by them, business persons understand the status of market and embrace new strategies to meet the customers' tastes and demands. Now a days e-commerce and digital marketing are popular.
        <br><br> Social media allow the users to share their thoughts and views, create their own content and receive the latest information and news. Online job portals have equally been popular these days, and both the jobseekers and the employers have found this platform to be very effective and economic. In fact, everything looks. easier to do with social media.
        <br><br>
        <strong>b. How do you compare virtual communication and face-to-face communication? </strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>	Communication comprises a sender, message and recipient. This process is completed when the receiver comprehends the sender's message to make conversation more comfortable and convenient.
        <br><br> In virtual communication a recipient doesn't need to be present. It lets us talk to people no matter what location they are in. It is more likely to be non-verbal. Using virtual communication helps us to keep in touch with people even if they are busy and not able to meet up. Various social network sites and apps are common platforms to have virtual communication. It's easier to organize and share all of the information we want when we communicate virtually.
        <br><br> Face to face communication needs both the sender and recipient to be present & respond immediately. When we talk to somebody face-to-face we can actively. notice their level of attention in our conversation. It helps us to build personal relationship and socialize. It prevents our communicative skills to be rusty, with our body language and tone. We can express what we want. Message can be easily understood by the concerned parties as both verbal and non-verbal ways. In-face-to face communication illiterate people also understand message that they don't. understand in written message. Conversation on the telephone or cell phone and chatting through internet are oral communication but cannot be termed as face to face communication. Body language, facial expression, gesture and eye contact also are very effective to convey messages.
        <br><br>
    </p>
