<h2>Answer these questions.</h2>
<h3>a.	Why is the Zhou Age called a feudal age? ( किन झुट युगलाई सामन्ती युग भनिन्छ ?)</h3>
<p>Ans.	The Zhou government bore a strong resemblance to some of the forms of feudalism in medieval Europe. China was composed of network of city-states loyal to the Zhou King, from which military and political control spread over the surrounding farming villages. </p>

<h3>b.	What is the location advantage of the Qin? ( 'किन्' को स्थानको फाइदा के हो? ) </h3>
<p>Ans. 	The territory of the Qin state in modern Shanxi province was well guarded from the east by mountains and gorges and had easy access to the north. China plain through the Yellow river passes. No major battle ever took place in the Qin's heart land.</p>

<h3>c.	What contributed to the success in the warfare as described in the text? ( यो Text मा वर्णन गरिए अनुसार युद्धमा सफलताको लागि के ले योगदान पुयायो ?)</h3>
<p>Ans. The location of the state, their size of the army, and their expert use of the chariot contributed to their success in warfare. </p>
<h3>d.	Why did the Qin invite the foreign advisor, Shang Yang? ( किन विदेशी सल्लाहकार Shang Yang लाई Quin ले आमन्त्रित गरे ?) </h3>
<p>Ans. 	The Qins invited the foreign advisor, Shang Yang to suggest them the idea of state policy and to maintain the strong impact and legalism, efficiency and strength of the state.</p>
<h3>e.	What were the key features of the Qin political system? (Qin राजनीतिक प्रणालीको मुख्य विशेषताहरू के थिए ?) </h3>
<p>Ans. Fear, control and brutal suppression to literate people, stupidity, executing of scholars were the key features of Qin dynasty political system.</p>
<h3>f. 	How were the people treated during the Qin period? (Qin अवधिमा मानिसहरूलाई कस्तो व्यवहार गरियो ?)</h3>
<p>Ans. 	During the Qin period, those who contributed the most in the state affairs were highly rewarded, while those who lived without work were sent to work as slave on Shi Huangdi's building projects such as the Great Wall of China the Grand Canal and the roads. </p>
<h3>g.	Why did Shi Huangdi stop educating ordinary people? ( किन Shi Huangdi ले साधारण मानिसहरूलाई शिक्षा दिन बन्द गरे ?)</h3>
<p>Ans. Shi Huangdi stopped educating ordinary people because be believed that the uneducated people were easier to control.</p>
<h3>h.	What did the Qin achieve by the legalism in practice? (व्यवहारमा कानुनीकरणले किन् ले हासिल गर्यो ?)</h3>
<p>Ans.The Qin achieved the efficiency and strength of the state, a superior army, a disciplined bureaucracy, and obedient populace and the unquestioned authority of a strong central government by the legalism in practice. </p>
<h3>i. Why did Shi Huangdi never sleep in the same room for two consecutive nights? (किन शि Huangdi लगातार दुई रातहरूको लागि एकै कोठामा कहिल्यै सुत्नु भएन् ?) </h3>
<p>Ans. 	Shi Huangdi never slept in the same room for two consecutive nights because of constant fear of assassination. </p>
<h3>j.	What are the everlasting works of the Qin Dynasty? (राजवंशको चिरस्थायी चिह्नहरु के हुन् ?)</h3>
<p>Ans.The everlasting works of the Quin Dynasty were: 
    <br>
<ul>
    <li>the standard of bureaucratic government and the legalistic policies</li>
    <li>a wonder of ancient art work. The Terracotta Army in Xian</li>
    <li>the Great Wall of China</li>
    <li>
        The Grand Canal and the roads which today link the cities of China and
        the country side.
    </li>
</ul>

</p>
<h2>Critical Thinking</h2>
<h3>a.	The Great wall and the Taj Mahal are the creation of the autocratic rulers. Present your view for or against this statement.</h3>
<p>Ans. In an autocracy power remains in the hands of a single person. The autocratic political system has the feature of fear and control. Absolute monarch and military dictators are the examples of autocracy. The great advantage to autocracy is that when immediate and certain action is necessary, serious decisions are quickly made and brought into action. Autocratic leaders usually make choices which rely on their ideas and judgements and hardly accept any advice from others from outside their own small circle.</p>
<P>The rulers are able to collect resources. Whatever seems important they order people to fulfil the vision. The autocrats have the army force as their sole power. They keep eyes on their people as well as protect from any invading neighbours. They establish rules themselves. Projecting any protest or objection on their vision  is a risky endeavour. Some of the great structures such as the Taj Mahal and the Great Wall have been the fancy of autocrats in the name of being immortal.</P>
<p>Commemorating a victory in battle, dedication to their loved ones, gaining popularity and employing unskilled and semiskilled labours, slavery system along with talented artisans, architects, the autocratic rulers created such wonders. </p>

<h3>b.	How do you describe the pros and cons of feudalism? </h3>
<p>Ans.	Feudalism is a social system prevailed in Europe during middle age in which  people (Vasslas were given land and protection by a noble man (lord) and had to work and fight for him in return. </p>
<p>
    <strong>Pros of Feudalism </strong><br>
i.	Feudal system had the provision of social and economic security to the lower class people.<br>
ii.	The landlord couldn't deprive the vassals of their land and had to care for them during disability.<br>
iii.	It helped to develop the qualities like loyalty, bravery, generosity, humility and courtesy.<br>
iv.	The vassals showed courteousness, loyalty, and humility to the lords, and in return the lords revealed love & bigheartedness to the vassals. <br>
v.	Feudalism established social & moral trends<br>
vi.	Feudal system showed the way for the rise of states in modern times.<br>
vii. Strong kingdom established.<br>
<strong>Cons of feudalism</strong><br>
<br>
i.	Feudalism brought class division in the society<br>
ii.	Poors led substandard life whereas rich and nobles led life with comforts and leisure.<br>
iii.	Possibility of slavery system<br>
iv.	No peaceful and steady government.<br>
v.	Absence of unity, no real sovereign states<br>
vi. Country could be united as a rivalry, suspicion and wars present.<br>


</p>

