<h2>Comprehension</h2>
<h3>A.	Write whether the following statements are True, False or Not Given. </h3>
<p>
    a. During the holidays, people eat and drink more than usual. - True <br>
    b. Getting too little exercise and eating too much is the reason why people put on weight. - <strong>True</strong><br>
    c. David Allison's research involved studying rats under laboratory conditions - <strong>False</strong><br>
    d. You may need to go shopping for clothes if you come down with a cold. - <strong>True</strong><br>
    e. Adenovirus-36 (AD-36) decreases the percentage of fat in the fat cells.  <strong>False</strong><br>
    f. Vaccination against infections could be used in the future to prevent obesity. -<strong> True</strong><br>
    g. People under severe stress can experience breathing difficulties. -<strong> True</strong><br>
    h. A study indicates that mice that have never been on a diet choose fatty food, when given a choice between high-calorie or low-calorie food products. -<strong> False</strong><br>
    i. Rajita Sinha has been studying the connection between brain activity and behaviour. - <strong>True</strong><br>
    j. Specific hormones regulate our appetite. - <strong>True</strong>
       
</p>

<h3>B. Answer the following questions</h3>
<h3>a.	In what sense are the holidays a time of excess? When can a person gain weight?</h3>
<P>Ans. 	The holidays are a time of exercise as people eat and drink more than usual. A person can gain weight when he/she overeats and does less exercise.</P>
<h3>b.	According to David Allison, which factor contributes to excess obesity?</h3>
<p>Ans. 	According to David Allison, the factors, such as light (Changes in the amount of time spent in light or dark environments), viruses (infection with adenovirus 36), endocrine disrupter chemicals, exposure to blue wavelengths at night, breathing polluted air and too little sleep contribute to exercise obesity.</p>
<h3>c.	What, according to Dhurandhar, can be the way of preventing fatness?</h3>
<p>Ans. According to Dhurandhar, vaccination against infection can be the way of preventing fatness.</p>
<h3>d.	What is the relationship between chill and obesity? How can saying 'om' help reduce fatness?</h3>
<p>Ans. Chill and obesity has disparate relation. Chill helps burn calories which decreases Fatness, but if we are not regularly exposed to cold, our brown fat deposits shrink and it cannot burn off the calories. As a result, a person happens to gain weight. According to Ranjit Sinha, stress increases craving for high calories food for those who have the habit of consuming them. She recommends mindfulness, stress reduction and meditation techniques to control thoughts and behaviour. Chanting 'OM is believed to reduce stress, relax our body and calm our mind which helps taking control over the urge and stress-related eating of high-calories food.</p>

<h3>e.	Why it is necessary to be careful while buying plastic packaged fatty foods?</h3>
<p>Ans. It is necessary to be careful while buying plastic packaged fatly foods. because they contain endocrine disruptive chemicals that can reach into food and drinks and cause the expansion of waist liners.</p>
<h3>f.	Why does Nelson suggest avoiding blue wavelengths of light at night?</h3>
<p>Ans. Nelson suggests avoiding blue wavelengths of light at night because they are known to be especially disruptive to the circadian system.</p>
<h3>g.	How does breathing polluted air affect one's fatness?</h3>
<p>Ans. Breathing polluted air can cause extra fat to accumulate around our stomach and also make our cells less sensitive to insulin.</p>
<h3>h.	What is the link between sleep and weight?</h3>
<p>Ans. Sleep plays a crucial role for gaining and losing the weight. Sleep deprivation reduces the secretion of leptin, a hormone that suppresses appetite, and increases levels of ghrelin, a hormone that stimulates appetite. Similarly, children aged between 3 and 5 who sleep less than the average of 11 hours a night were found to be overweight or obese.</p>

<h2>Critical thinking</h2>
<h3>a.	What do you do you to keep yourself fit? What food do you avoid and why?</h3>
<p>Ans. I go jogging or cycling every morning. I also do exercise and yoga at home. I have recently joined a gym too. Every Friday I play futsal. I try to maintain balance between work and rest. 1 sleep on time and wake up early.
    <br>
    I avoid junk food and meat. I also avoid sugar containing foods. I avoid these foods since they are likely to increase fat in the body. Overconsumption of these foods can increase pressure and cholesterol level. This is why, I eat organic and home made foods. I give priority to milk, fruit, and green vegetables. </p>

<h3>b.	Healthy citizens are the greatest asset of a country. What can a state do to keep her citizen healthy?</h3>
<p>Ans. The greatest natural wealth of a nation is her people. Her success relies on how healthy they are. Sound health makes a significant contribution in the speedy and robust economic progress, as healthy population lives longer and are more productive.</p>
<P>The country which doesn't give emphasis on the health of the citizens is proven to have poor economic growth rate. Hence, it is important to prioritize quality health care system. Every citizen should have an easy and affordable access to proper health facilities.</P>

<p>Both the state and the individual have an equal role in ensuring the health of nation. Government should provide quality health, nutritious food, adequate water supply, sanitary system and basic health infrastructure to her citizen. Healthy communal behaviours should be promoted. Prevention of the communicable disease should be kept as the most important agenda in the development planning People should be protected from environmental health hazards. There should be provision of easy health services. More number of health centres & hospitals should be established in the remote parts of the country.</p>

<h2>Writing</h2>
<h3>a.	Yoga can be good to stay physically and mentally healthy. Do you practise any yoga? Write an essay on the benefits of yoga.</h3>
<p>Ans. Yoga is a Sanskrit word which means union and discipline. It is an old art in which body is connected with mind. It is a type of exercise through which all the elements: of body are linked with mind with the help of meditation and relaxation. In simple, it is the act of emptying the mind to have interaction with the inner self. Body and soul get connected through this breathing exercise. Moreover, a balance between body and soul is possible only through yoga. One lears to control movement of different organs of body thereby linking body with soul.</p>
<P>Yoga is very beneficial exercise because one can control his or her body through meditation. It is a rich source of releasing stress and anxiety. It teaches discipline and unity. Furthermore, it strengthens our soul and gives us sweet feelings of healthiness. Not to mention, it sharpens our wit and improve our intelligence. It enhances social well-being and help to connect us with nature and its beauty releases the negative thought and finish element of negativity. It develops a high level of patience and confidence. It is a best form of exercise to mention good health. It boosts our intelligence. Last but not the least, it prevents us from different diseases, especially respiratory disorders.</P>

<h3>b.	How can a person be mentally healthy? Provide about ten tips to a person to stay mentally fresh and healthy.</h3>
<p>By doing regular exercise and practicing yoga, a person can be mentally healthy. Exercise keeps our brain and other vital organs fit. Having said that it is also significant in improving mental health.</p>
<p>Ten tips to stay mentally fresh and healthy are:</p>
<p>i. Taking care of one's physical health.<br>
    ii. Getting fresh air and exposure to sunlight<br>
    iii. Being mindful<br>
    iv. Spending time with people whose company one enjoys<br>
    v. Avoiding obesity<br>
    vi. Managing stress.<br>
    vii. Doing regular exercise<br>
    viii. Avoiding alcohol, smoking, chewing tobacco.<br>
    ix. Eating less but adequate nutritious food<br>
    x. Keeping a balance between rest &work<br>
    </p>
<h2>Grammar</h2>
<h2>Concord/subject-verb agreement</h2>
<p>Subject-verb agreement is the correspondence of a verb with its subject in person (first, second, or third) and number (singular or plural).. </p>
<h3>A. 	Read this text and notice the subject-verb agreement.</h3>
<p>The human body is like a machine. All machines need fuel to give them energy. The fuel for the human body is food. Most of the energy comes from two substances in our food: carbohydrates and fats. Carbohydrates are found in food like potatoes, bread, rice, wheat, corn, etc. and sugar. Fats come from food like meat, oil, cheese and butter. All junk food contains lots of carbohydrates and fats. If you eat a lot of junk food, you will probably get fat and it may cause a lot of diseases.</p>
<h3>B.	Complete the sentences by choosing the correct verbs from the brackets. </h3>
<p>a.	Everyone... (has/have) problems in their life Countries also...... (has/have) problems, and so...... (do/does) the world. One of the greatest problems (is/are) the growing population. The population in some countries...... (is/are) huge.</p>
<p>Ans. Everyone has problems in their life. Countries also have problems, and so does the world. One of the greatest problems is the growing population. The population in some countries is huge.</p>
<P>b.	A number of my friends (love loves) riding bicycles, but neither my brother nor my sister (own/owns) a cycle. At 4 o'clock, either my mother or father...... (is/are) coming to pick me up in a car.</P>
