    <h2>Ways with words</h2>
    <h3>A. Find the meanings of the following words and phrases from a dictionary and make sentences by using them.</h3>
    <p>peep into, pop down, remarkable, hedge, wonder,
        tumble,
        doze off, earnestly, tiny, creep
    </p>
    <p>
        1. <strong>peep into - </strong> to get a quick look into something<br>
        <strong>Ans: </strong> I <u>peeped into</u> the window to see what was being done in the room.<br><br>
        2. <strong>pop down - </strong>to go somewhere quickly <br>
        <strong>Ans: </strong> I <u>popped down</u> to the shop to have some coffee.<br><br>
        3. <strong>remarkable -</strong> unusual, surprising excellent or worthy of notice<br>
        <strong>Ans: </strong> The interior of the house is <u>remarkable.</u> <br><br>
        4. <strong>hedge -</strong> a row of bushes or small trees planted close together along the edge of a garden,
        field or road.<br>
        <strong>Ans: </strong> Two rabbits are springing in the <u>hedge.</u><br><br>
        5. <strong>wonder - </strong>desire to know something<br>
        <strong>Ans: </strong> I <u>wonder</u> why she left the job. <br><br>
        6. <strong>tumble - </strong>to fall quickly without control <br>
        <strong>Ans: </strong> She lost her footing and <u>tumbled</u> down the stairs.<br><br>
        7. <strong>doze off -</strong> to sleep, especially during the day.<br>
        <strong>Ans: </strong> He <u>dozed off</u> in the office because of tiredness.<br><br>
        8. <strong>earnestly - </strong>Seriously<br>
        <strong>Ans: </strong> She <u>earnestly</u> hopes to come back in summer.<br><br>
        9. <strong>tiny - </strong>very small <br>
        <strong>Ans: </strong> Look at her <u>tiny</u> fingers. Aren't they cute?<br><br>
        10. <strong>Creep - </strong>to move slowly, quietly and carefully in order to avoid being heard or noticed.
        <br>
        <strong>Ans: </strong>She <u>crept</u> up the stairs, trying not to wake them up.

