    <h2>Comprehension</h2>
    <h3>Answer these questions.</h3>
    <p>
        <strong>a. How did Mahabir Pun begin his lifelong journey in Nepal after coming back to Nepal from the
            US?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>Mahabir Pun began his lifelong journey in Nepal by staying in his home village Nangi of
        Myagdi district and helping villagers start a high school as a volunteer teacher.<br><br>
        <strong>b. Why didn't he want to work for other companies in the US or in Nepal?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>He wanted to work independently. He wanted to do something in his own way for the benefits
        of human beings. That's why he did not want to work for other companies in the US or in Nepal.<br><br>
        <strong>c. Why did he involve in innovation? </strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>He involved in innovation because he wanted to find solution of social problems existing
        in the communities.<br><br>
        <strong>d. What are the income-generating programmes that he helped to start?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>He helped to start income generating programmes, like paper making, jam making, cheese
        making and handicrafts making, by using local resources. <br><br>
        <strong>e. Whose support is Pun getting proceed with his campaign?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>Main support is coming from people and communities. Local people, father's group, mother's
        group, local clubs and many innovative young people support him getting to proceed with his campaign.<br><br>
        <strong>f. How have the developed countries become prosperous?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>Developed countries have become prosperous by their new invention. They have given topmost
        priority for research and invention for economic development. <br><br>
        <strong>g. How can we keep the most talented and innovative people in Nepal?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>By creating sound environment and support system in innovation and research and creating
        good opportunity to find job, we can keep the most talented and innovative people in Nepal.<br><br>
    </p>
    <h2>Critical Thinking</h2>
    <p>
        <strong>a. Pun says, "We do not have culture of innovation that encourages young people to be innovative and
            creative. Do you agree with him? Explain.</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>Encouraging invention, research, and creativity in young people is essential to the
        development of any country. Education is the glorious means with the formidable mission of preparing today's
        youth for tomorrow's society. But in our country. educational institutions don't necessarily quip the young
        graduates with a culture of innovation. The majority of the Nepalese youths leave studying at a premature stage
        since they don't see a sound environment and future in their education system. <br><br>Some youths who continue
        their study go abroad in search of better opportunities. The young population should receive maximum
        encouragement for their inventive and creative capacity. It is essential to identify those ways and means of
        promoting conditions favourable to the development of potentially innovative talents. Educational institutions,
        government, vocational schools, and educated citizenry should create the environment to encourage invention and
        research. By developing the sense of responsibility, strengthening the spirit of initiative, encouraging the
        critical attitude we can make them involve in innovative project. If they can find suitable platform, and
        guarantee of handsome income, they will get motivated to stay back in Nepal and do research and invention. It is
        our responsibility to create sound environment and support system to keep the most talented and innovative
        people and use them for the economic development of Nepal.<br><br>
        <strong>b. What qualities does an individual need to become an entrepreneur? </strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>The process of setting up a business is known as entrepreneurship. An entrepreneur is an
        individual who creates a new business, bearing most of the risks and enjoying most of the rewards. S/he is
        usually seen as an innovator, a source of new ideas. goods, services, and business. Moreover, she is known as a
        source of new ideas or innovators, and bring new ideas in the market by replacing old with a new invention. The
        starting point of entrepreneurship is the desire to set up and run a business independently. But along with it
        comes some other qualities too. Curiosity, time management, strategic thinking. efficiency, resilience,
        communication skill, networking, strong finance, and branding are very essential requirements. In addition, the
        following characteristics make a successful entrepreneur:
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Ability to take a risk- </strong>Starting any new venture involves a considerable amount of failure
            risk. Therefore, an entrepreneur needs to be courageous and able to evaluate and take risks, which is an
            essential part of being an entrepreneur.</li>
        <li><strong>Innovation- </strong>One should be highly innovative to generate new ideas, start a company and earn
            profits out of it.</li>
        <li><strong>Visionary and Leadership quality- </strong>To be successful, the entrepreneur should have a clear
            vision of his/her new venture. Leadership quality is paramount because leaders impart and guide their
            employees towards the right path of success.</li>
        <li><strong>Open-Minded-ness- </strong> In a business, every circumstance can be an opportunity and used for the
            benefit of a company. Hence, one should be open to everything. </li>
        <li><strong>Flexibility- </strong>An entrepreneur should be flexible and open to change according to the
            situation. To be on the top, a businessperson should be equipped to embrace change in a product and service,
            as and when needed.</li>
        <li><strong>Know your Product- </strong>A company owner should know the product offerings and also be aware of
            the latest trend in the market. It is essential to know if the available product or service meets the
            demands of the current market, or whether it is time to tweak it a little: Being able to be accountable and
            then alter as needed is a vital part of entrepreneurship.</li>
    </ul>
    </p>
