    <h2>Comprehension</h2>
    <h2>Answer question</h2>
    <h3>a. Why was the Italian Socialist Mergari treated like a madman?</h3>
    <p><strong>Ans: </strong>Italian socialist Mergari was treated like a madman because he had spoken a few natural
        human words.</p>
    <h3>b. Can political aims be attained by the criminal instrumentality of war? If yes, how?</h3>
    <p><strong>Ans: </strong>Yes, political aims can be attained by criminal instrumentality of war. The politicians are
        war profiteers. They are only concerned with the outcome of mass slaughter. They use criminal instrumentality of
        war to achieve power and gain. According to the writer, the bigger, the bloodier, the more destructive the
        battles. the less will be accomplished for the future, the less hope there will be of appeasing hatreds and
        rivalries.
    </p>
    <h3>c. Which hopes and plans were said to be mutually contradictory?</h3>
    <p><strong>Ans: </strong>The hopes and plans related to war, mass slaughter and suppression of people for the sake
        of humanity, peace and prosperity were said to be mutually contradictory.
    </p>
    <h3>d. What can be the sacred duty of every man of good will on earth?</h3>
    <p><strong>Ans: </strong>The sacred duty of every man of good will on earth can be to prevent the final catastrophe
        (war).</p>
    <h3>e. Is it good to tacitly accept war as an instrument of politics? If not, what else should be done?</h3>
    <p><strong>Ans: </strong>No, it is not good to tacitly accept was as an instrument of politics. Politicians should
        not engage in war, rather they should accept things as they come, rejoice in victories and should deplore the
        losses in their own camp. Moreover, we must not close our cars to the dire warning of this hour, the threat of
        such unthinkable horrors.
    </p>
    <h3>f. How can we stop war in the world?</h3>
    <p><strong>Ans: </strong>If each one of us opens his heart to it, if each one of us firmly resolves to serve the
        cause of peace, to communicate his thoughts and intimations of peace if every man of good will decides to devote
        himself exclusively for a little while to clearing away the obstacles, the barriers to peace, then we can stop
        war in the world.
    </p>
    <h3>g. What is the main message of this essay?</h3>
    <p><strong>Ans: </strong>The main message of this story is that we have to establish and keep peace in the world by
        stopping wars.</p>
    <h2>Critical thinking</h2>
    <h3>a. Are warmongers the greatest enemies for peace? What do you want to suggest to them?</h3>
    <p><strong>Ans: </strong>A warmonger is a strong supporter of war. Moreover, he advocates or stirs up war. He can
        appear to promote peace in some activities but still be a warmonger at heart. The Warmongers apply a false and
        unreal ideology to break the harmony and peace of the country. They want to seize property, land and treasures
        by creating hatred among groups and compelling them to be involved in war. They are the reasons for the loss of
        peace in the world. I want to suggest that they engage in creative discussions to reach an agreement rather than
        choosing the path of violence.
    </p>
    <h3>b. The Nobel Prize Winner American novelist John Steinbeck (1902-1968) once said, "All war is a symptom of man's
        failure as a thinking animal". Do you agree with the novelist? Why?</h3>
    <p><strong>Ans: </strong>I agree with the novelist. War is the worst thing in the world. It gives benefit to none.
        It causes immense loss of human life and resources on part of both the winning country as well as the losing
        country. When we forget reasoning and humanity and instead follow animal instincts, we fail to use the advantage
        we have as a thinking creature.</p>
    <h3>c. Does any war end all wars and bring lasting peace to the world? Discuss.</h3>
    <p><strong>Ans: </strong>The one-word answer for this is no. Not a single war can bring about lasting peace by
        ending other wars. Instead, it creates a new kind of war among people. The new. war gives rise to new enemies
        and fresh personal grudges. Peace is the solution to war not another war.
    </p>
    <h3>d. Why do you think countries go in wars even though they have their own boundaries?</h3>
    <p><strong>Ans: </strong>It is because war doesn't respect political or territorial boundaries. But there is a
        policy gap across borders where statehood and diplomacy can struggle to reach. A country doesn't respect the
        other's sovereignty, independence and dignity, which creates a feeling of animosity among people. Some big
        countries are power hungry. Their greed and lust for dominance is also responsible for them to go into wars.
    </p>
    <h2>Writing</h2>
    <h3>Write essays in about 500 words on the following topics.</h3>
    <p><strong>a. War and peace</strong></p>
    <p>
        <strong>Ans: </strong>War is a terrible evil. It refers to an armed battle between nations. War causes big
        sufferings to the family members of the people who die during the war. During wars, there is massive destruction
        of property, wealth, trade, industry, etc. It completely upsets the social life of people.<br><br>
        Many people argue that war is a necessary evil, and the only process of solving international disputes. But, in
        reality, war happens, only because people are not ready to settle disputes in a peaceful manner.<br><br>
        Peace means complete freedom from disturbance. It refers to those times when there is no war or fight among
        nations. Once the world starts believing that wars are unnecessary and decide to abolish war completely, they
        will certainly find a way for peaceful co-existence.<br><br>
        Human being's love for peace is universal. Human beings are by nature peaceful. War does not furnish a proof of
        the idea that humans are fighting animals. Even the acts of war did not spoil the least human's spontaneous love
        for peace.<br><br>
        Modern people are threatened by the dreadful inventions of science. But this actual threat is coming not from
        science but from war, in which the power of science is abused. It is one thing to keep a nation strong and
        vigorous and save it, it is another thing to infuse a wanton spirit of aggression and destruction into
        it.<br><br>
        The modern nations must truly realize in their heart the full significance of the teaching- 'For all they that
        take to the sword, shall perish with the sword'. Then and then only shall peace reign in the world.

    </p>
    <p><strong>b. Responsive youths for peace and prosperity</strong></p>
    <p>
        <strong>Ans: </strong>Youths are the pillars of peace and tranquility in the world. The threat of nuclear power
        has been killing our peace of mind, happiness and our wish to live. It has affected man's life directly or
        indirectly. Even slight misuse of atomic energy may bring about horrible changes in climate, biological
        structure, ecological system and finally annihilate the world.<br><br>
        Let the youths make a special request for providing advice, help with setting up courses and conferences on
        world peace to assist in workshops and peace education for the youth. Youth must be encouraged to appeal to the
        world leader to create a peaceful and sustainable world. The exercise of human rights and freedom is an
        essential element of peace. Peace is an essential requirement for the satisfaction of human basic needs such as
        food, shelter, health, education, security, labour and environment.<br><br>
        We know that there are a large number of youths missing the proper training and education for good productive
        jobs, very few jobs and too many non-productive employment with poor payment and security the country can't
        obtain prosperity. The world community should invest much money in applicable skills, trainings. suited to the
        job market should provide them.<br><br>
        Growing awareness of the interdependence of the world and of global problems is of concern to all people of the
        world. Without a creative and innovative mind, we can't achieve prosperity. So, every nation should create an
        environment of creative tasks and research for the benefit of human beings.
    </p>
    <h2>Grammar</h2>
    <h2>Sentence functions</h2>
    <h3>A.	Do you know the parts of a sentence? If not, look at this sentence.</h3>
    <p>
        The fat man painted the door green last week.<br>
    In this sentence, the fat man- Subject (S) <br>
    painted- Verb (V)<br>
    the door- Object (0)<br>
    green- Complement (C)<br>
    last week- Adverbial (A)
    </p>
    <h3>B. 	Divide the following sentences into different parts.</h3>
