        usually - adverbial<br>
        wears - verb<br>
        glasses - object<br><br>
        (e)	They elected him President.<br><strong>Ans: </strong>
        They - subject<br>
        elected - verb<br>
        him - indirect object<br>
        President - direct object<br><br>
        (f)	Rabin is laughing. <br><strong>Ans: </strong>
        Rabin-subject<br>
        is laughing - verb<br><br>
        (g)	He has a big house in Butwal.<br><strong>Ans: </strong>
        He- subject <br>
        has- verb<br>
        big- adjective<br>
        house- object <br>
        Butwal- complement<br><br>
        (h)	The man who lives next door is a professor.<br><strong>Ans: </strong>
        The man- subject <br>
        who lives next door- adverbial/clause<br>
        is- verb<br>
        a professor- object<br><br>
        (i)	Her uncle has been living in Kathmandu for fifteen years.<br><strong>Ans: </strong>
        Her uncle- subject<br>
        has been living- verb<br>
        in- preposition <br>
