    <p><strong>Ans: </strong>(See Answer a. above for the definition of globalization.) <br>
        It goes without saying that globalization has impacted almost every walks of our life. The social values seem to
        be clearly affected by the global culture. The cultural practices, like food habit, housing, fashion, and social
        etiquettes, have drastically changed. Basic indigenous norms and values are at the verge of extinction. For
        instance, in Nepal, the youngsters prefer junk foods to home made dishes. Social media culture is flourishing at
        an unstoppable speed. the process and progress of education
    </p>
