    <p><strong>Ans: </strong>Globalization is a process, which has affected many areas of human life, one of those being
        education. In the twentieth century, many developing countries have experienced growth in the educational
        facilities available to them due to the entry of institutions from the West. Some believe that this process is
        an invaluable opportunity for the people of the developing countries to raise their skills and standards of
        education. Others fear that it is merely a modem version of cultural imperialism that will lead to the creation
        of a universal, ultimately Western society: Through Globalization of education, which is being knowledge
        transfer from the Western countries into developing countries, is intended to improve the skills and
