      <strong>b.	As a thing of art nothing could be more admirable than the painting itself. Explain. </strong><br>
      <strong>Ans. </strong>It is said that a painting can tell a thousand words. As a matter of fact, painting is a very special form of art. It involves the process making an image on paper or canvas. The artists fill life into it, which impacts our thoughts and emotions directly. It can touch us in many ways.<br><br>
      <strong>c.	A more intense look at the painting reveals the illusion. Have you noticed any such painting? </strong><br>
      <strong>Ans. </strong>Yes, I have noticed such painting. It was the portrait of Icarus falling into the sea by Brueghel. I came to make meanings of many illusive ideas expressed in that painting after having a deep observation of the same. One of such discoveries was the illusion of indifference and inhumanity.<br><br>
    </p>
