        <strong>Ans. </strong>At first, Makar did not admit his crime of killing the merchant as he had an attitude of not admitting his guilt. However, his heart melted when he heard Aksionov's 26 year-long suffering because of the mischief he had not committed. In addition, Aksionov also forgave Makar despite his unpardonable sins and did not report the latter's secret plan to the authorities.<br><br>
