        <strong>a. Why do the two soldiers spend their free time on Sundays away from the barracks out in the
            countryside?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>Maupassant's male leads, Luc Le Ganidec and Jean Kerderen, are two French soldiers and
        very good friends, who adore spending their weekends together away from their barracks and urban setting. The
        countryside destination reminds them of their homes. They are attracted to the fields, the hedges, the forests,
        and beaches. However, the centre of their attention is the dairy maid from the village of Bezons. <br><br>
        <strong>b. Why does the girl become the topic of conversation for these soldiers? </strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>One of the centres of attraction in the two French soldiers' outing is a tall young
        village girl. The beautiful country maid brings her cow out to pasture every week at the same time. They start
        conversing about her as both of them are secretly in love with her.<br><br>
        <strong>c. Why does deception enter into their friendship?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>Luc Le Ganidee starts seeing the country maid without Jean's knowledge. Hence, love for
        the girl is responsible for the entrance of deception into their friendship.<br><br>
        <strong>d. Do you think that Luc is a betrayer of friendship?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>I feel Luc is a great betrayer of friendship. He puts the friendship built in trust at
        risk for the sake of a newly found girl. Moreover, his dishonesty and deception also costs the life of an
        innocent person, in addition to their friendship.<br><br>
        <strong>e. What is the cause of suicide of Jean? Do you think that it was the only release of his
            love?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>The secret betrayal, on the hand of Luc and the village girl, is the cause of Jean's
        suicide. I think it was the bitterness of both friendship and love, which led to such tragic
        consequence.<br><br>
    </p>
    <h2>Reference to the context</h2>
    <p>
        <strong>a. What is the central theme of the story?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>The central theme of this story is love and friendship. The writer wishes to show that
        friendship becomes fragile in the presence of love.<br><br><br>
        <strong>b. "What are you doing here? Are you watching the grass grow?"</strong><br>
        <strong>i. Who is the speaker?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>The village milkmaid is the speaker.<br><br>
        <strong>ii. What does the word "here" indicate?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>"Here" indicates the pasture in the countryside, where the two Bezons soldiers are
        spending their day off.<br><br>
        <strong>iii. Who does "you" refer to? </strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>"You" refers to the two French soldiers.<br><br><br>
        <strong>c. "He leaned-he-he was leaning-so far over-that his head carried him away and-he-fell--he
            fell-"</strong><br>
        <strong>i. Who is the speaker?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>Luc is the speaker.<br><br>
        <strong>ii. Why is the speaker speaking with interruption?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>The speaker speaking with interruption because he is devastated by the untimely death of
        his friend, which was caused by his insensitiveness and deception.<br><br>
        <strong>iii. What does he mean when he says "he-fell-he fell--"?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>He means to say that Jean fell into the stream.<br><br><br>
        <strong>d. Two Little Soldiers' can be viewed as a series of dramatic scenes. Describe the story as tragedy.
        </strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>Two Little Soldiers' is a modern western short story, by a French novelist, poet,
        essayist, travel writer, short story writer and author. Guy de Maupassant. It is a tragic love story involving
        three people. The plot ends with the separation of two good friends: Luc and Jean. Similarly, the love story
        between the village girl and Jean does not produce good results, thanks to the betrayal of the girl in question
        and Luc. Most importantly, an innocent person has to become the victim of dishonesty in friendship and love. All
        these elements establish Maupassant's story as a tragedy.<br><br><br>
        <strong>e. What is the setting and style of the story?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>Two Little Soldiers' is a modern western short story, by a French novelist, poet,
        essayist, travel writer, short story writer and author. Guy de Maupassant. The majority of the story takes place
        in Courbevole, a town in the countryside of France. The time setting of the story is not specified. The writer
        has adopted a realistic writing style. His subjects are real common day subjects, like soldier, war, love,
        friendship, jealousy, and deception. He uses the omnipresent narrator to serve the best angle possible to
        narrate the realistic descriptions.<br><br><br>
        <strong>f. How would you describe the conflict between the friends?</strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>‘Two Little Soldiers' centres on the conflict between two good friends, Luc and Jean.
        Maupassant relies on the psychological conflict rather than the physical one. The entrance of a woman becomes
        the main cause of this sort of silent mental hostility. Luc betrays the bond of friendship to win the lady. As a
        result, a fierce internal bitterness prevails in the relationship between the male lovers, which breaks their
        friendship. Luc's attempt to access the girl costs a friendship and a life.<br><br><br>
    </p>
    <h3>Reference beyond the text</h3>
