        <strong>Ans. </strong>Maupassant's story describes a conflict between friendship and love. One has to sacrifice
        the former for the sake of the latter, exemplified by Luc in the story. In the triangular love relationship, the
        third person can suffer if two attendees start maintaining hidden enterprise. The writer suggests that a person
        and his best friend cannot love the same person. Otherwise, tragic consequences, like the ones in the story, may
        take place.<br><br>
        <strong>b. How would you describe the triangular love? </strong><br>
        <strong>Ans. </strong>‘Two Little Soldiers' is a modern western short story, by a French novelist, poet,
        essayist, travel writer, short story writer and author, Guy de Maupassant. One of the major areas of the
        writer's focus is the triangular love. It is clear that the author is not a great fan of such a story. In the
        triangular love relationship, the third person can suffer if two attendees start maintaining hidden enterprise.
        The writer suggests that a person and his best friend cannot love the same person. Otherwise, tragic
        consequences, like the ones in the story, may take place. Hence, honesty is a must in a relationship, whether it
        is two-faceted or triangular.<br><br>
    </p>
