        as simile, symbolism, imagery, alliteration, and assonance.</h3>
    <p><strong>Ans: </strong>Burns' poem is full of literary devices. The most prominent device of all is simile. It is
        a figure of speech which indirectly compares one thing with another thing of a different kind, using the words
        'like' or 'as'. "O my Luve is like a red, red rose", "O, my love is like the melody" and "As fair art thou, my
