        nations, as well as overall international systems at social, cultural, ecological, economic and psychological
        levels. Some individuals have to die in war. Others sustain permanent injuries. Either way, their families are
        left with abundant materials to grieve or mourn the rest of their lives. In addition, war hampers social
        cohesion and the feeling of universal brotherhood. Economy of the defeated nation suffers hugely. Sovereignty
        and independence is at stake. Political instability is likely to take over. The relation between or among the
        communities or nations are severed.<br> War can influence positively too. Firstly, the weak and problematic
        governance systems can be eliminated. Educational, medical and technical progress can be mapped too. Employment
