    <h2>Reference to the context</h2>
    <h3>a. Explain the following:</h3>
    <p><strong>Ans: Poverty is looking into a black future.</strong>The above given line is extracted from a modern
        western essay entitled "What is Poverty?", by an American essayist, Jo Goodwin Parker. Using examples drawn from
        her own person experience, the author explains the meaning of poverty in this essay. In this extract, she
        focuses on a particular aspect of poverty.<br><br>
