    </h3>
    <p><strong>Ans: Homelessness<br></strong>You ask me what is homelessness? Listen to me. Here I am, dirty, smelly,
        and with no "proper" cloth on and with the stench of my rotting teeth near you. I will tell you. Listen to me.
        Listen without pity. I cannot use your pity. Listen with understanding. Put yourself in my dirty, worn out,
        ill-fitting shoes, and hear me. Homelessness is getting up every morning on the lane of a cold street. It is
